Section 1 – Definitions.

Adapted Material means material that is derived from or based upon the Licensed Material and in which the Licensed Material is translated, altered, arranged, transformed, or otherwise modified in a manner requiring permission under the Copyright and Similar Rights held by the Licensor.

Commercial Purposes means acting primarily for or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation.

